@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Call Center Management System";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Introduction</h1>
    <p>
        The call center management system deals with management of call centers. This system is user friendly and flexible 
        to maintain with minimum data entry and availability of information on request with response in seconds.
    </p>
    <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Home/ABout">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Aim</h2>
        
        <p class="lead">
            The call center management system 
            is aimed at securing call center system in a cashless envirnment, whereby it generates a 7 digits code for each
            user calling the center. Each customer must be able to provide the code (7 digits known to the user alone) which may
            be asked randomly by the call center representative.
        </p>
        <p><a href="Home/ABout" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Objectives</h2>
        <ul class="lead list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Having customers information</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Assigning the 7 didgits code to all old users</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Assigning the 7 digits to new users as soon as they have their new account</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Provision of additional level of security</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Part of the 7 digits code would be randomly requested for, from the user by the customer care representative</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Home/ABout">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Verification Questions</h2>
        <p class="lead">The following information can be used for the first authentication.</p>
        <ul class="lead">
            <li class="list-group-item">Name of the caller</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Contact Details</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Access Code or Pin</li>
        </ul>
        <dl class="lead">
            <dt>Name of the Caller</dt>
            <dd>The caller has to provide his/her name which must match the record on the account. 
            The account might have only one name, which is the account holder's or several such has in the case of a family or company
            </dd>
            <dt>Contact and Personal Details</dt>
            <dd>
                The next data to verify is several of the contact and personal details on record. It can be an address (residential, business or billing address), 
                phone number, or email address. At times, security guidelines will allow verification of details of the account-holder such as birth-date, place of 
                birth, mother's maiden name, etc.
            </dd>
            <dt>Access Code or Pin</dt>
            <dd>
                An account pin of 7 digit would be assigned by default to customer at the start of the account activation. Sometimes, the access code can be a 
                combination of letters and numbers known only to the account owner.
            </dd>
        </dl>
        <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Customer/Index">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
    </div>
</div>